Irish Loan Conditions Won’t Be Eased, Katainen Tells Finnish YLE

-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 
2011-02-25T07:29:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/irish-loan-conditions-won-t-be-eased-katainen-tells-finnish-yle.html
Ireland’s bailout loan conditions
won’t be changed to reduce the number of measures the Irish are
expected to take to fix their finances,  Finland ’s Finance
Minister Jyrki Katainen told state-owned broadcaster YLE.  Finland won’t agree to changing the terms of the loans,
Katainen told Helsinki-based YLE.  “There is an understanding in  Europe  and the euro area 
that the requirements can’t be eased in a way that would endanger 
the work to bring the Irish economy back to health,” Katainen 
told YLE.  Click here for web link in Finnish  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
